1. Service-Oriented: Their work history (sales associate, cashier, housekeeper) and volunteer work as a personal care worker suggests someone who genuinely enjoys helping others.

2. Patient and Empathetic: Their experience helping non-English speaking customers and working with elderly/disabled individuals as a caregiver indicates patience and understanding.

3. Detail-Oriented: Multiple mentions of being "neat and well organized" and their housekeeping experience suggests someone who pays attention to detail and values orderliness.

4. Reliable: The consistent emphasis on basic duties and responsibilities across jobs suggests someone who takes pride in doing routine tasks well.

5. Humble: The straightforward, no-frills description of duties without embellishment suggests someone who is modest and honest about their capabilities.

6. Adaptable: Their diverse work experience (from retail to caregiving to housekeeping) shows someone who can adjust to different work environments.

7. Hard-Working: The mix of physical work (housekeeping) and customer service roles suggests someone who isn't afraid of putting in effort, whether mental or physical.

8. Growth-Minded: Their experience training new cashiers and being a "self-starter" indicates someone willing to take on additional responsibilities and help others learn.

The resume appears to be from someone who values stability, takes pride in service-oriented work, and has a strong work ethic, even if they might not be the most polished professional.
